MULATION FAILED - %0d MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME %0d", stats1.errors, stats1.errortime);\n        end\n\n        if (stats1.errors_pm) $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has %0d mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time %0d.", "pm", stats1.errors_pm, stats1.errortime_pm);\n        else $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has no mismatches.", "pm");\n        if (stats1.errors_hh) $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has %0d mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time %0d.", "hh", stats1.errors_hh, stats1.errortime_hh);\n        else $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has no mismatches.", "hh");\n        if (stats1.errors_mm) $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has %0d mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time %0d.", "mm", stats1.errors_mm, stats1.errortime_mm);\n        else $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has no mismatches.", "mm");\n        if (stats1.errors_ss) $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has %0d mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time %0d.", "ss", stats1.errors_ss, stats1.errortime_ss);\n        else $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has no mismatches.", "ss");\n\n        $display("Hint: Total mismatched samples is %1d out of %1d samples\\n", stats1.errors, stats1.clocks);\n        $display("Simulation finished at %0d ps", $time);\n        $display("Mismatches: %1d in %1d samples", stats1.errors, stats1.clocks);\n    end\n\nendmodule\n</testbench>\n')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='\nThe module interface is given below:\n<module_interface>\nmodule TopModule (\n    input  logic clk,\n    input  logic reset,\n    input  logic ena,\n    output logic pm,\n    output logic [7:0] hh,\n    output logic [7:0] mm,\n    output logic [7:0] ss\n);\nendmodule\n</module_interface>\n')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.ASSISTANT: 'assistant'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='{\n    "reasoning": "1. **Requirements Analysis**: The goal is to implement a 12-hour clock with BCD output for hours (01-12), minutes (00-59), and seconds (00-59), plus a PM indicator. The reset is synchronous and high-priority, resetting the clock to 12:00:00 AM.\\n2. **BCD Representation**: Each output (hh, mm, ss) is 8 bits, representing two BCD digits. For example, 59 seconds is represented as `8\'h59` (binary `0101_1001`).\\n3. **Counter Design**: \\n    - **Seconds**: A counter that increments from 00 to 59. When it reaches 59 and `ena` is high, it rolls over to 00 and triggers a minute increment.\\n    - **Minutes**: A counter that increments from 00 to 59. When it reaches 59 and `ena` is high, it rolls over to 00 and triggers an hour increment.\\n    - **Hours**: A counter that increments from 01 to 12. When it reaches 12 and `ena` is high, it rolls over to 01 and toggles the PM flag.\\n4. **PM Logic**: The PM flag toggles when the hour rolls over from 12 to 01. Specifically, 12:59:59 AM -> 01:00:00 AM (PM remains 0), and 12:59:59 PM -> 01:00:00 PM (PM becomes 1). Wait, the standard 12-hour clock logic is: 12:59:59 AM transitions to 01:00:00 AM. 11:59:59 AM transitions to 12:00:00 PM. Let\'s refine: \\n    - Hours sequence: 12 -> 1 -> 2 ... -> 11 -> 12. \\n    - PM toggles when the hour moves from 11 to 12? No, PM is 1 during 12:00:00 PM to 11:59:59 PM. \\n    - Let\'s track PM: At 12:00:00 AM, PM=0. At 12:00:00 PM, PM=1. \\n    - The transition from 11:59:59 to 12:00:00 is when the PM flag toggles.\\n    - Correction: In a 12-hour cycle (12, 1, 2, ..., 11), the PM flag should toggle when the hour rolls over from 11 to 12 (if we consider 12 as the start of the cycle) or from 12 to 1. Let\'s use the convention: 12:00:00 AM (PM=0), 01:00:00 AM ... 11:59:59 AM, 12:00:00 PM (PM=1), 01:00:00 PM ... 11:59:59 PM. \\n    - So, PM toggles when the hour transitions from 11 to 12.\\n5. **Implementation Details**: \\n    - Use BCD counters (two 4-bit nibbles) for seconds, minutes, and hours to simplify logic.\\n    - Reset state: hh=12 (BCD `8\'h12`), mm=00, ss=00, pm=0.\\n6. **Syntax Advice**: Use `always @(*)` for combinational logic and `always @(posedge clk)` for sequential logic. Use `logic` for all signals. Ensure BCD values are assigned correctly (e.g., `hh = {h_tens, h_ones}`).",\n    "module": "module TopModule (\\n    input  logic clk,\\n    input  logic reset,\\n    input  logic ena,\\n    output logic pm,\\n    output logic [7:0] hh,\\n    output logic [7:0] mm,\\n    output logic [7:0] ss\\n);\\n\\n    // BCD Counters\\n    // ss_ones, ss_tens, mm_ones, mm_tens, hh_ones, hh_tens\\n    logic [3:0] ss_ones, ss_tens;\\n    logic [3:0] mm_ones, mm_tens;\\n    logic [3:0] hh_ones, hh_tens;\\n    logic       pm_reg;\\n\\n    // Reset logic and increment logic\\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\\n        if (reset) begin\\n            // Reset to 12:00:00 AM\\n            hh_tens <= 4\'d1;\\n            hh_ones <= 4\'d2;\\n            mm_tens <= 4\'d0;\\n            mm_ones <= 4\'d0;\\n            ss_tens <= 4\'d0;\\n            ss_ones <= 4\'d0;\\n            pm_reg  <= 1\'b0;\\n        end else if (ena) begin\\n            // Seconds counter\\n            if (ss_ones == 4\'d9 && ss_tens == 4\'d5) begin\\n                ss_ones <= 4\'d0;\\n                ss_tens <= 4\'d0;\\n                \\n                // Minutes counter\\n                if (mm_ones == 4\'d9 && mm_tens == 4\'d5) begin\\n                    mm_ones <= 4\'d0;\\n                    mm_tens <= 4\'d0;\\n                    \\n                    // Hours counter\\n                    if (hh_ones == 4\'d9 && hh_tens == 4\'d11) begin // This is not quite right for 12-hour BCD\\n                        // Let\'s handle hours more carefully\\n                    end\\n                end else begin\\n                    // ...\\n                end\\n            end else begin\\n                // ...\\n            end\\n        end\\n    end\\n\\n    // Redoing the logic for clarity and correctness\\n    // We will use standard integers for calculation and convert to BCD at the end to avoid complexity,\\n    // or just use BCD logic directly.\\n    \\n    logic [5:0] hour_val; // 1 to 12\\n    logic [5:0] min_val;  // 0 to 59\\n    logic [5:0] sec_val;  // 0 to 59\\n    logic       pm_val;\\n\\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\\n        if (reset) begin\\n            hour_val <= 6\'d12;\\n            min_val  <= 6\'d0;\\n            sec_val  <= 6\'d0;\\n            pm_val   <= 1\'b0;\\n        end else if (ena) begin\\n            if (sec_val == 6\'d59) begin\\n                sec_val <= 6\'d0;\\n                if (min_val == 6\'d59) begin\\n                    min_val <= 6\'d0;\\n                    if (hour_val == 6\'d12) begin\\n                        hour_val <= 6\'d1;\\n                        pm_val <= ~pm_val;\\n                    end else if (hour_val == 6\'d11) begin\\n                        hour_val <= 6\'d12;\\n                        pm_val <= ~pm_val;\\n                    end else begin\\n                        hour_val <= hour_val + 1;\\n                    end\\n                end else begin\\n                    min_val <= min_val + 1;\\n                end\\n            end else begin\\n                sec_val <= sec_val + 1;\\n            end\\n        end\\n    end\\n\\n    // Convert to BCD for output\\n    // hh (01-12), mm (00-59), ss (00-59)\\n    always @(*) begin\\n        ss = { (ss_val_bcd_tens), (ss_val_bcd_ones) }; // dummy\\n    end\\n\\n    // Let\'s use the BCD approach correctly from the start.\\n    // Actually, the simplest way is to use internal counters and convert to BCD.\\n    \\n    logic [5:0] h_cnt, m_cnt, s_cnt;\\n    logic       p_cnt;\\n\\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\\n        if (reset) begin\\n            h_cnt <= 6\'d12;\\n            m_cnt <= 6\'d0;\\n            s_cnt <= 6\'d0;\\n            p_cnt <= 1\'b0;\\n        end else if (ena) begin\\n            if (s_cnt == 59) begin\\n                s_cnt <= 0;\\n                if (m_cnt == 59) begin\\n                    m_cnt <= 0;\\n                    if (h_cnt == 12) begin\\n                        h_cnt <= 1;\\n                        p_cnt <= ~p_cnt;\\n                    end else if (h_cnt == 11) begin\\n                        h_cnt <= 12;\\n                        p_cnt <= ~p_cnt;\\n                    end else begin\\n                        h_cnt <= h_cnt + 1;\\n                    end\\n                end else begin\\n                    m_cnt <= m_cnt + 1;\\n                end\\n            end else begin\\n                s_cnt <= s_cnt + 1;\\n            end\\n        end\\n    end\\n\\n    // Correcting the 12-hour PM toggle logic:\\n    // 12:00:00 AM (p=0) -> 01:00:00 AM ... -> 11:59:59 AM -> 12:00:00 PM (p=1) -> 01:00:00 PM ... -> 11:59:59 PM -> 12:00:00 AM (p=0)\\n    // The transition that toggles PM is 11:59:59 -> 12:00:00.\\n\\n    // Final Clean Implementation\\n    logic [5:0] h_reg, m_reg, s_reg;\\n    logic       p_reg;\\n\\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\\n        if (reset) begin\\n            h_reg <= 6\'d12;\\n            m_reg <= 6\'d0;\\n            s_reg <= 6\'d0;\\n            p_reg <= 1\'b0;\\n        end else if (ena) begin\\n            if (s_reg == 6\'d59) begin\\n                s_reg <= 6\'d0;\\n                if (m_reg == 6\'d59) begin\\n                    m_reg <= 6\'d0;\\n                    if (h_reg == 6\'d12) begin\\n                        h_reg <= 6\'d1;\\n                        // No PM toggle here (12:59:59 AM -> 01:00:00 AM)\\n                    end else if (h_reg == 6\'d11) begin\\n                        h_reg <= 6\'d12;\\n                        p_reg <= ~p_reg; // 11:59:59 AM -> 12:00:00 PM\\n                    end else begin\\n                        h_reg <= h_reg + 1;\\n                    end\\n                end else begin\\n                    m_reg <= m_reg + 1;\\n                end\\n            end else begin\\n                s_reg <= s_reg + 1;\\n            end\\n        end\\n    end\\n\\n    // Actually, let\'s check the PM requirement: \\"The signal \'pm\' is asserted if the clock is PM, or is otherwise AM.\\"\\n    // 12:00:00 PM is PM. 12:00:00 AM is AM.\\n    // Standard sequence: 12 AM, 1 AM, ..., 11 AM, 12 PM, 1 PM, ..., 11 PM.\\n    // PM toggles when transitioning from 11:59:59 to 12:00:00.\\n    \\n    // Wait, looking at the testbench, it checks if reset is 12:00:00 AM. \\n    // Let\'s use the BCD logic directly to avoid any ambiguity.\\n\\n    logic [3:0] h_tens_reg, h_ones_reg;\\n    logic [3:0] m_tens_reg, m_ones_reg;\\n    logic [3:0] s_tens_reg, s_ones_reg;\\n    logic       pm_out_reg;\\n\\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\\n        if (reset) begin\\n            h_tens_reg <= 4\'d1;\\n            h_ones_reg <= 4\'d2;\\n            m_tens_reg <= 4\'d0;\\n            m_ones_reg <= 4\'d0;\\n            s_tens_reg <= 4\'d0;\\n            s_ones_reg <= 4\'d0;\\n            pm_out_reg <= 1\'b0;\\n        end else if (ena) begin\\n            // Seconds\\n            if (s_ones_reg == 4\'d9 && s_tens_reg == 4\'d5) begin\\n                s_ones_reg <= 4\'d0;\\n                s_tens_reg <= 4\'d0;\\n                // Minutes\\n                if (m_ones_reg == 4\'d9 && m_tens_reg == 4\'d5) begin\\n                    m_ones_reg <= 4\'d0;\\n                    m_tens_reg <= 4\'d0;\\n                    // Hours\\n                    if (h_tens_reg == 4\'d1 && h_ones_reg == 4\'d2) begin\\n                        h_tens_reg <= 4\'d0;\\n                        h_ones_reg <= 4\'d1;\\n                        // 12:59:59 AM -> 01:00:00 AM (PM stays 0)\\n                    end else if (h_tens_reg == 4\'d1 && h_ones_reg == 4\'d1) begin\\n                        h_tens_reg <= 4\'d1;\\n                        h_ones_reg <= 4\'d2;\\n                        pm_out_reg <= ~pm_out_reg; // 11:59:59 AM -> 12:00:00 PM\\n                    end else if (h_tens_reg == 4\'d0 && h_ones_reg == 4\'d9) begin\\n                        h_tens_reg <= 4\'d1;\\n                        h_ones_reg <= 4\'d0;\\n                    end else begin\\n                        // Incrementing BCD hours (01-12)\\n                        if (h_ones_reg == 4\'d9) begin\\n                            h_ones_reg <= 4\'d0;\\n                            h_tens_reg <= h_tens_reg + 1;\\n                        end else begin\\n                            h_ones_reg <= h_ones_reg + 1;\\n                        end\\n                    end\\n                end else begin\\n                    if (m_ones_reg == 4\'d9) begin\\n                        m_ones_reg <= 4\'d0;\\n                        m_tens_reg <= m_tens_reg + 1;\\n                    end else begin\\n                        m_ones_reg <= m_ones_reg + 1;\\n                    end\\n                end\\n            end else begin\\n                if (s_ones_reg == 4\'d9) begin\\n                    s_ones_reg <= 4\'d0;\\n                    s_tens_reg <= s_tens_reg + 1;\\n                end else begin\\n                    s_ones_reg <= s_ones_reg + 1;\\n                end\\n            end\\n        end\\n    end\\n\\n    // Let\'s simplify the hour BCD increment. The values are 01, 02, ..., 09, 10, 11, 12.\\n    // Actually, the simplest way to manage BCD is to use an integer counter and convert to BCD.\\n\\n    logic [5:0] h_cnt_int, m_cnt_int, s_cnt_int;\\n    logic       p_cnt_int;\\n\\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\\n        if (reset) begin\\n            h_cnt_int <= 6\'d12;\\n            m_cnt_int <= 6\'d0;\\n            s_cnt_int <= 6\'d0;\\n            p_cnt_int <= 1\'b0;\\n        end else if (ena) begin\\n            if (s_cnt_int == 6\'d59) begin\\n                s_cnt_int <= 6\'d0;\\n                if (m_cnt_int == 6\'d59) begin\\n                    m_cnt_int <= 6\'d0;\\n                    if (h_cnt_int == 6\'d12) begin\\n                        h_cnt_int <= 6\'d1;\\n                        // 12:59:59 AM -> 01:00:00 AM. PM doesn\'t change.\\n                    end else if (h_cnt_int == 6\'d11) begin\\n                        h_cnt_int <= 6\'d12;\\n                        p_cnt_int <= ~p_cnt_int; // 11:59:59 AM -> 12:00:00 PM\\n                    end else begin\\n                        h_cnt_int <= h_cnt_int + 1;\\n                    end\\n                end else begin\\n                    m_cnt_int <= m_cnt_int + 1;\\n                end\\n            end else begin\\n                s_cnt_int <= s_cnt_int + 1;\\n            end\\n        end\\n    end\\n\\n    // Convert h_cnt_int, m_cnt_int, s_cnt_int to BCD\\n    always @(*) begin\\n        ss = { (s_cnt_int / 10), (s_cnt_int % 10) }; // This is not quite right for BCD bit-width\\n    end\\n\\n    // Correct BCD conversion:\\n    always @(*) begin\\n        ss = { 4\'d0, 4\'d0 };\\n        ss[3:0] = s_cnt_int % 10;\\n        ss[7:4] = s_cnt_int / 10;\\n\\n        mm[3:0] = m_cnt_int % 10;\\n        mm[7:4] = m_cnt_int / 10;\\n\\n        hh[3:0] = h_cnt_int % 10;\\n        hh[7:4] = h_cnt_int / 10;\\n        \\n        pm = p_cnt_int;\\n    end\\n\\nendmodule"\n}')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='\nThe error below has been reported by the format tool:\n<format_error>\n{\n    "stdout": "",\n    "stderr": "./output_t22b_gemma4_26b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob141_count_clock/rtl.sv:94: error: Unable to bind wire/reg/memory `ss_val_bcd_tens\' in `TopModule\'\\n./output_t22b_gemma4_26b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob141_count_clock/rtl.sv:94: error: Unable to bind wire/reg/memory `ss_val_bcd_ones\' in `TopModule\'\\n./output_t22b_gemma4_26b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob141_count_clock/rtl.sv:94: error: Concatenation/replication may not have zero width in this context.\\n./output_t22b_gemma4_26b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob141_count_clock/rtl.sv:277: error: Concatenation operand \\"(s_cnt_int)/(\'sd10)\\" has indefinite width.\\n./output_t22b_gemma4_26b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob141_count_clock/rtl.sv: